cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with decentralized distributed systems and auto-scaling algorithms. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the behavior of nodes in a distributed system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper analyzes the behavior of a system and proposes algorithms for tuning it. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes numerical algorithms for approximating minimum bounds. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper analyzes the performance of the auto-scaling algorithm.
